- Double-check the neighbor counting in the `count_neighbors()` function to make sure it's accurate. Incorrect counting can lead to unexpected behavior in the automata.

- Verify that `initialize_grid()` is creating a good initial mix of live (wall) and dead (floor) cells. A grid that's too sparse or too dense may not develop interesting patterns.

- Ensure that `tilemap.set_cell(tile_index, position)` is actually drawing the tiles correctly and your TileMap node has the right tileset assigned with floor and wall tiles at the right indices. If there is an issue with drawing, it could give the appearance that the tiles are disappearing when, in fact, they are not being drawn correctly.

- Run the game and observe the console to see if any errors are being printed that might indicate problems elsewhere in your code.

